Doctor Jana du Plessis (R) and Doctor Anele Mtanjana (L) stand at the entrance of a resuscitation area where an intubox for worker safety designed is stored at the Charlotte Maxeke Hospital in Johannesburg, on April 15, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - Two more coronavirus related deaths have been reported in South Africa. Both deceased are from the Western Cape. This brings the number of COVID-19 related deaths in the country to 50. Explainer: New amendments to the lockdown regulations As of Friday night, the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is 2, 783. There have been 100, 827 deaths conducted. Gauteng has broken the thousand mark with 1, 018 infections reported. Western Cape (717) KwaZulu Natal (591) Eastern Cape (246) and and Free State (100). For an updated number of cases, click here. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.